Uses of Package
com.i2group.apollo.alertfeedretrievalservice.transport

  • Packages that use com.i2group.apollo.alertfeedretrievalservice.transport 
    Package Description
    com.i2group.apollo.alertfeedretrievalservice
    The i2 Analyze alert feed retrieval service provides clients with the ability to retrieve alert feeds and determine which ones they are subscribed to.

    Calls to methods in this service must include a SOAP header containing an element named <ApolloMetadata> with an attribute named TimeZone. The value of the TimeZone attribute indicates the time zone that the client requires dates and times to be sent and displayed in.
    com.i2group.apollo.alertfeedretrievalservice.transport
    Contains classes for the service that retrieves alert feeds from the Analysis Repository.
  • Classes in com.i2group.apollo.alertfeedretrievalservice.transport used by com.i2group.apollo.alertfeedretrievalservice 
    Class and Description
    AlertFeedSearchResults
    Contains the AlertFeedInfos and other information that form the results of a search for alert feeds.
  • Classes in com.i2group.apollo.alertfeedretrievalservice.transport used by com.i2group.apollo.alertfeedretrievalservice.transport 
    Class and Description
    AlertFeedInfo
    Information that describes an alert feed to a client, including the ItemIdentifier of the feed, the ItemIdentifier of the Item (or ItemPlaceholder) being monitored, and an indication of how the current user receives alerts from the feed.
